formatDescription: Standard Data Format (SDF) files are commonly used to transfer data between different programs. SDF files are formatted ASCII text files, in which fields are delimited with a particular character (usually a space), and each record ends with a carriage return and/or line feed.
provenanceCompoundName: National Library of Australia / National Library of Australia
